X,Y
\langle \cdot, \cdot \rangle
\Sigma
\Omega
 \langle \Sigma X,Y \rangle \cong \langle X, \Omega(Y) \rangle  \,\,\, ? 
(X,x_0)
\Sigma X=\left(X\times [-1,1]\right)/\left((x,1)\equiv (x_0,t)\equiv (x,-1)\text{ for all }x\in X,t\in [-1,1]\right)
\equiv
\Omega X=\{f:[0,1]\to X:f(0)=x_0=f(1)\}
\phi:\left\langle \Sigma X,Y \right\rangle\cong \left\langle X,\Omega Y\right\rangle
\left(\phi(f)(x)\right)(t)=f(x,t)
